dt1IdTable.name: dt1IdTable
dt1IdTable.description: A table that contains information that identifies the hardware and software that make up the specified dual T1 card.

dt1IdEntry.name: dt1IdEntry
dt1IdEntry.description: There is one entry in this table for every dual T1 card in the chassis.

dt1IdIndex.name: dt1IdIndex
dt1IdIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the dual T1 card for which this row in the table pertains. The value of this index matches the value of the index for the corresponding entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

dt1IdHardwareSerNum.name: dt1IdHardwareSerNum
dt1IdHardwareSerNum.description: The dual T1 card's hardware serial number as stored in EEPROM.

dt1IdHardwareRev.name: dt1IdHardwareRev
dt1IdHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the specified dual T1 card as stored in its EEPROM.

dt1IdSoftwareRev.name: dt1IdSoftwareRev
dt1IdSoftwareRev.description: The revision of the software being executed in the specified dual T1 card.

dt1CfgTable.name: dt1CfgTable
dt1CfgTable.description: The Dual T1 Card Configuration Table contains an entry for each of the manageable Dual T1 Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current configuration of parameters that affect the operation of all the entities that reside on the given card.

dt1CfgEntry.name: dt1CfgEntry
dt1CfgEntry.description: There is one Dual T1 Card Configuration table entry per Dual T1 Card in the chassis.

dt1CfgIndex.name: dt1CfgIndex
dt1CfgIndex.description: A unique value for each Dual T1 Card in the chassis. The value of dt1CfgIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding Dual T1 Card entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

dt1CfgSpanATmgSrcPrio.name: dt1CfgSpanATmgSrcPrio
dt1CfgSpanATmgSrcPrio.description: Identifies the priority at which the clock recovered from span line A is to be used as this Dual T1 Card's transmit timing source.

dt1CfgSpanBTmgSrcPrio.name: dt1CfgSpanBTmgSrcPrio
dt1CfgSpanBTmgSrcPrio.description: Identifies the priority at which the clock recovered from span line B is to be used as this Dual T1 Card's transmit timing source.

dt1CfgInternTmgSrcPrio.name: dt1CfgInternTmgSrcPrio
dt1CfgInternTmgSrcPrio.description: Identifies the priority at which this Dual T1 Card's internal clock is to be used as the transmit timing source.

dt1CfgTdmBusTmgSrcPrio.name: dt1CfgTdmBusTmgSrcPrio
dt1CfgTdmBusTmgSrcPrio.description: Identifies the priority at which the clock currently on the TDM bus is to be used as this Dual T1 Card's transmit timing source.

dt1CfgIdleDiscPatt.name: dt1CfgIdleDiscPatt
dt1CfgIdleDiscPatt.description: Idle disconnect pattern sent to the modems. Normal values: USA = 1, international = 84. Default = 1. Configure the modems identically. Consult the help screen, user manual or US Robotics before changing.

dt1CfgNumT1TypeNacs.name: dt1CfgNumT1TypeNacs
dt1CfgNumT1TypeNacs.description: The number of T1 and/or T1/E1-PRI NACs in the chassis. Default=multiple(3).

dt1CfgCallEventFilter.name: dt1CfgCallEventFilter
dt1CfgCallEventFilter.description: This objects provides a means to filter the types of call event traps generated. It specifies the class of calls to filter out. Default = filterOutSuccess(4).

dt1CfgSetDs0OutofService.name: dt1CfgSetDs0OutofService
dt1CfgSetDs0OutofService.description: This object determines to put DS0s out of service upon removal Quad Modem NAC when fixed modem routing method is engaged. Default = disable(2).

dt1CfgWirelessMode.name: dt1CfgWirelessMode
dt1CfgWirelessMode.description: This object will configure the wireless mode of operations of the T1 at power up. Default = normal(1).

dt1StatTable.name: dt1StatTable
dt1StatTable.description: The Dual T1 Card Status table contains an entry for each of the manageable Dual T1 Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current card specific status. Status values dynamically change during calls, and they are read-only.

dt1StatEntry.name: dt1StatEntry
dt1StatEntry.description: There is one Dual T1 Card Status entry per Dual T1 Card in the chassis.

dt1StatIndex.name: dt1StatIndex
dt1StatIndex.description: A unique value for each Dual T1 Card in the chassis. The value of dt1StatusIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding Dual T1 Card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

dt1StatCurrentTmgSrc.name: dt1StatCurrentTmgSrc
dt1StatCurrentTmgSrc.description: Based on the availability of the various timing sources and the current settings of the priorities at which they are to be used, the Dual T1 Card will select the current transmit timing source. This object will indicate the current timing source being used for transmit timing.

dt1StatSelfTest.name: dt1StatSelfTest
dt1StatSelfTest.description: This object contains the result of the last self test command requested from the command table. It includes both destructive and non destructive results.

dt1StatUpTime.name: dt1StatUpTime
dt1StatUpTime.description: This object contains the uptime of the NAC

dt1StatCallEventCode.name: dt1StatCallEventCode
dt1StatCallEventCode.description: This object contains the definition of the call event codes sent in the call event trap.

dt1StatCallEventQ931Value.name: dt1StatCallEventQ931Value
dt1StatCallEventQ931Value.description: This object contains the Q931 Call Reference Value sent in the call event trap.

dt1CmdTable.name: dt1CmdTable
dt1CmdTable.description: The Dual T1 Card Command table contains an entry for each of the manageable Dual T1 Cards in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more Dual T1 cards in the NAS chassis. The number of entries in this table is given by the value of dt1IdNumber.

dt1CmdEntry.name: dt1CmdEntry
dt1CmdEntry.description: There is one Dual T1 Card Command entry per Dual T1 Card in the chassis.

dt1CmdIndex.name: dt1CmdIndex
dt1CmdIndex.description: A unique value for each Dual T1 Card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding Dual T1 Card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

dt1CmdMgtStationId.name: dt1CmdMgtStationId
dt1CmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with dt1CmdReqId and dt1CmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

dt1CmdReqId.name: dt1CmdReqId
dt1CmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command or test on this Dual T1 Card. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

dt1CmdFunction.name: dt1CmdFunction
dt1CmdFunction.description: This object contains a value which describes the command which is being invoked.

dt1CmdForce.name: dt1CmdForce
dt1CmdForce.description: In some cases, the Dual T1 Card may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, this object can be set to force in a subsequent issue of the command to cause the command to be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

dt1CmdParam.name: dt1CmdParam
dt1CmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no aditional parameters required.

dt1CmdResult.name: dt1CmdResult
dt1CmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

dt1CmdCode.name: dt1CmdCode
dt1CmdCode.description: The value of this object upon command completion indicates a further description of what went wrong if the command was unsuccessful. In the case of tests, a bit mapped result of each of the sub-tests performed can be found in the status table.

dt1TrapEnaTable.name: dt1TrapEnaTable
dt1TrapEnaTable.description: Table containing objects to enable traps on the Dual T1 Cards in the chassis.

dt1TrapEnaEntry.name: dt1TrapEnaEntry
dt1TrapEnaEntry.description: There is one entry for each Dual T1 Card in the chassis.

dt1TrapEnaIndex.name: dt1TrapEnaIndex
dt1TrapEnaIndex.description: A unique index identifying the Dual T1 Card to which the trap enable objects pertain.

dt1TrapEnaTxTmgSrcSwitch.name: dt1TrapEnaTxTmgSrcSwitch
dt1TrapEnaTxTmgSrcSwitch.description: An object which enables the SNMP proxy agent to generate a trap upon detection of the Dual T1 Card switching to an alternate transmit timing source. Default = disableAll(2).

dt1TrapEnaCallEvent.name: dt1TrapEnaCallEvent
dt1TrapEnaCallEvent.description: This object enables the generation of an SNMP trap to track calls entering and exiting the NAC. Default = disableAll(2).

dt1TrapEnaCallArriveEvent.name: dt1TrapEnaCallArriveEvent
dt1TrapEnaCallArriveEvent.description: This object enables the generation of an SNMP trap to track call arrivals the NAC. Default = disableAll(2).

dt1TrapEnaCallConnEvent.name: dt1TrapEnaCallConnEvent
dt1TrapEnaCallConnEvent.description: This object enables the generation of an SNMP trap to track call connects. Default = disableAll(2).

dt1TrapEnaCallTermEvent.name: dt1TrapEnaCallTermEvent
dt1TrapEnaCallTermEvent.description: This object enables the generation of an SNMP trap to track normal call terminations. Default = disableAll(2).

dt1TrapEnaCallFailEvent.name: dt1TrapEnaCallFailEvent
dt1TrapEnaCallFailEvent.description: This object enables the generation of an SNMP trap to track failed call terminations. Default = disableAll(2).
